<br>
Druids and wizards tend to frown on that solution, claiming how young druids/wizzies make their income on porting, how it should be an ability exclusive to their class, and how spreading porting abilities among other resources (say, making the nexus insta-port) dilutes the wizard class as it stands.  If this is NOT a common protest, correct me, but I was under the impression that it was.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, Verant has introduced horses which move ~ at bard speed for a price/mob drop.  The last I checked, bard speed was an ability exclusive to bards.  The same casters who so staunchly maintain that defining class abilities should be sacred when it comes to PORTING happily indulge in purchasing landspeed which was once the domain of bards.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong; I don't mind sharing my bardspeed with others.  I'd just like to get my back scratched in return.  Gimme a porting option the equivalent of the horse.  Maybe a cute little spaceship or invisible jet or something.<br>
<br>
Personally, I don't think that any class can begin to complain about the duties imposed on them by the game unless they are a rezzer.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Everything else is a little less demanding after that.<br>
<br>
But yeah, while I may not have been a porter, I've played an enchanter through the baby levels till 49 (escaping the kei and c2 insanity, but getting my share of random &quot;clarity me&quot; tells from orc 1 when I am in the nexus, tells across DL, etc.), and I've helped a number of people on insane crs because they have lost track of their corpse.  (This phenomenon seems to occur more frequently on new servers.  got a bunch of requests on kb.)  I have also paid the price of NOT being a porter; having to run 10 zones and wait on 2 boats on crs, etc.  I try not to be a burden to porters I know are busy, but if there are un-anon porters in the zone I am in, will I shoot them a tell?  Sure.<br>
<br>
This game requires porting if you want to get something done in less than 5 hours.  I've personally tested it.  If you don't like being harrassed about it, have them take the necessity of it out of the game.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Or, like I said, make it a luxury open to all classes, and an easily accessible skill for a couple.<br>
<br>
~Kat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uleopapanthera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leopa Panthera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/16/02 3:48:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3139.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Kite !</span><hr size=1> I think more classes should get ports, I really do. I was thrilled when faithstones started to come out and certain items would let you gate to certain places. I did backflips when you could bind in the firepots.<br>
<br>
I can see why wizards would complain because they do TWO things -- nuke and port. It's understandable so I allow leeway for those gripes.<br>
<br>
From what I understand, druids complain because it &quot;waters&quot; down our need for them. They're pissy about other class getting R3, horses, j/tboots, and so on. They've come up with lists of items with right clicks on them and claim that it nerfs their classes even more and makes them unneeded. (You know it's bad when a few of them complain about soulbinders.) The list goes on and on. I'm not as tolerant of their complaints about porting as I am about wizards.<br>
<br>
I agree with you that we need to reduce the demand for ports in the game. Using the Nexus spires was a great start. Now if they would just make it so that we can bind melees in Timorous Deep! (That should be moot when PoP comes out! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
I do hear your frustrations and I agree with you. <p><center><a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/bnorrathsstudio"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/leopa/sigs/gotsig.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>O.G. (Original Gnome)</span><br>  Posts: 1486<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/16/02 5:01:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3139.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-side-01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Kite !</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Druids and wizards tend to frown on that solution, claiming how young druids/wizzies make their income on porting<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->There are maybe four or five wizards or druids who ever say this. The rest of us would like them to shut the hell up and just save up some fucking fine steel weapons to sell like the rest of us did. Just doing faction work tonight in GD, I made more money than professional port whores could at the same hour (midnight PST).<br>
<br>
Yeah, it's a watering down thing. If my class does two things, don't give one of them away.<br>
<br>
But I hear ya about VI making it less necessary. The answer isn't to make ports everywhere: It's to make it so you don't NEED a port. Norrath is designed with dead zones to travel through -- the Karanas, OOT, TD, 90 percent of the Iceclad Ocean -- which are almost totally void of content, and only serve to say &quot;gee, look, this is a big world!&quot; In practice, it's a nuisance. It would be easy to design all the appropriate level contact contiguous to each other, so that people could move out quite naturally as they level up, still keeping the same home base. Sort of like, well, what every expansion since has done, to a greater or lesser degree. VI needs to get off the fucking pot and retool the old world the same way. The Karanas are a JOKE to other MMORPG developers, and it's pathetic that VI can't figure out how to make people WANT to go to OOT, despite all the rich possibilities that lie there. (And, hell, make the druid ring work there again -- as a way to encourage the traffic.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uniliz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>niliz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/16/02 6:30:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3139.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane of Kite !</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> And Evade is no thx to us casters.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
